  "prompt": "What books should every teenager read?",
  "response": "There are many books that can have a profound impact on teenagers, offering valuable lessons, insights, and perspectives. Here\u2019s a list of essential reads across various genres that are often recommended for teenagers:\n\n1. **\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee**\n   - A profound commentary on racial injustice and moral growth.\n\n2. **\"The Catcher in the Rye\" by J.D. Salinger**\n   - An exploration of teenage angst and alienation.\n\n3. **\"The Great Gatsby\" by F. Scott Fitzgerald**\n   - A look at the American Dream and the complexities of love and wealth.\n\n4. **\"1984\" by George Orwell**\n   - A dystopian novel that explores themes of totalitarianism and surveillance.\n\n5. **\"The Perks of Being a Wallflower\" by Stephen Chbosky**\n   - A coming-of-age story that captures the highs and lows of adolescence.\n\n6. **\"The Fault in Our Stars\" by John Green**\n   - A touching story of love and loss that deals with life, death, and everything in between.\n\n7. **\"Lord of the Flies\" by William Golding**\n   - An exploration of human nature and society through the lens of stranded boys on an island.\n\n8. **\"The House on Mango Street\" by Sandra Cisneros**\n   - A series of vignettes depicting the life of a Latina girl growing up in Chicago.\n\n9. **\"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho**\n   - A motivational tale about following dreams and listening to one's heart.\n\n10. **\"Speak\" by Laurie Halse Anderson**\n    - A powerful story about a teenage girl dealing with trauma and finding her voice.\n\n11. **\"Harry Potter Series\" by J.K. Rowling**\n    - A fantasy series that teaches about friendship, bravery, and the fight against evil.\n\n12. **\"The Giver\" by Lois Lowry**\n    - A thought-provoking dystopian novel about conformity, choice, and the importance of emotions.\n\n13. **\"Simon vs. the Homo Sapiens Agenda\" by Becky Albertalli**\n    - A heartfelt story about identity, love, and friendship in a modern high school setting.\n\n14. **\"Eleanor & Park\" by Rainbow Rowell**\n    - A beautiful story of first love and the struggles of growing up.\n\n15. **\"The Diary of a Young Girl\" by Anne Frank**\n    - A poignant account of a young girl's life during the Holocaust that emphasizes resilience and hope.\n\nThese books can encourage critical thinking, empathy, and a deeper understanding of the world, making them valuable reads for teenagers.",
